f the Senate’s most powerful advocates for the health and safety of America’s citizens. He championed seemingly minor, unglamorous reforms that made a big difference to everyday lives, from raising the national drinking age to preventing domestic abusers from purchasing guns. These campaigns earned him powerful enemies in the alcohol, tobacco, and firearms industries, and he was subjected to some of the most brutal campaign mudslinging in American history. Yet, as this inspiring biography reveals, New Jersey’s longest-serving senator was not afraid to take big political risks if it meant standing up for his principles, whether that meant opposing the Iraq War or protecting LGBTQ and women’s rights.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 7aBIOGRAPHY & AUTOBIOGRAPHY / General.2bisacsh  aFrank R. Lautenberg, politics, american politics, policy, biography, history, paterson, new jersey.1 aBiden, Joe, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aClinton, Hillary, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKatz, Daniel E., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aOlin, Dirk, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertRutgers University Press Complete eBook-Package 2024z978311079131040uhttps://doi.org/10.36019/978197883801740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781978838017423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781978838017/original  a978-3-11-079131-0  Rutgers University Press Complete eBook-Package 2024b2024  aEBA_EMB  aGBV-deGruyter-alles